&lt;h5&gt;Location&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will have a hybrid work schedule and when in the office could work out of any of the 45 Benesch locations. The following locations have an aviation team and or focus on aviation business development:&amp;nbsp; Atlanta, GA, Denver, CO, 4 locations throughout Nebraska (Bellevue, Grand Island, Lincoln, Omaha) and 4 locations throughout Kansas (Kansas City, Wichita, Topeka, Manhattan), and Kansas City, MO. Remote work will be considered.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;The Impact You Will Have&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design responsibility for elements such as pavement, drainage, utilities, lighting/NAVAIDS, security and fuel facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for project design calculation files, ensuring adequate independent quality control reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the process of compiling and coordinating plans, specifications, cost estimates and pay items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and review drafting and the assembly of plan sets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and oversee task work plans for assigned team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in active team communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize technical meetings among design staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform occasional field construction observation, sometimes requiring out-of-town travel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active involvement in professional organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
